\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {MT head-set filtering ablation on held-out word-aligned dev examples.} To make the all-head baseline maximally charitable, we average the candidate head set first and then restrict the argmax to the source-prompt token zone before scoring against gold aligned source tokens. Scores are reported in points ($100\times \mathrm  {TS}$). Even under this source-only argmax, the per-direction retained top-8 heads still preserve a markedly stronger alignment signal than uniform all-head averaging.\relax }}{10}{table.caption.27}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:mt-head-filtering}{{4}{10}{\textbf {MT head-set filtering ablation on held-out word-aligned dev examples.} To make the all-head baseline maximally charitable, we average the candidate head set first and then restrict the argmax to the source-prompt token zone before scoring against gold aligned source tokens. Scores are reported in points ($100\times \mathrm {TS}$). Even under this source-only argmax, the per-direction retained top-8 heads still preserve a markedly stronger alignment signal than uniform all-head averaging.\relax }{table.caption.27}{}}
